headline.main: NAZI 'PEACE PLANS' DERIDED IN LONDON; British View Papen's 'Feeler' as Part of German Campaign to Lull Turkey's Fears

lead_paragraph: LONDON, Nov. 17 -- There is a general belief among those who study such subjects here that the reported declaration of Frans von Papen, German Ambassador in Ankara, and other stories about the possibility of peace that emanate from Turkey all are part of a German plan.
